definition.value: The surgical removal of a cyst.
Note: cystectomy can refer to removal of bladder OR removal of a cyst.
The surgical removal of an ovarian cyst.
The surgical removal of a cyst from the kidney.
A test to detect streptococcus, either Group A or Group B, in a patient.
A rapid antigen detection test to diagnose bacterial pharyngitis caused by group A streptococci.
A diagnostic procedure used to evaluate an individual's ability to perceive and judge the relative distances of objects in the three-dimensional world.
Therapy that helps with processing, integrating or organizing sensory information of the body.

value.value: Collection of stratum corneum samples by applying adhesive tape to the skin.
An intervention, e.g. a breathing or oral device, to help keep a person's airways open while they sleep.

definition.value: Transplantation of fetal tissue into a person to treat disease.
A non invasive procedure that uses magnetic fields to stimulate nerve cells in the brain.
Examining chromosomes to identify abnormalities.
A genetic test that compares DNA sample to normal control to look for genetic alterations.
Assessing specific variants within a gene or genes that thave been associated with a condition.
Testing a single gene for genetic sequence changes.
A diagnostic procedure that analyzes multiple genes at once to idenify genetic variants associated with specific diseases or conditions.
Examination of methylation patheway genes.

value.value: A laboratory method that involves analyzing free (i.e., non-cellular) DNA contained within a biological sample. Most often, clinicians are looking for genomic variants associated with hereditary disorders.

definition.value: Procedures and treatments that are used to aid in achieving pregnancy conception in individuals who are having difficulty doing so spontaneously.
Use of an ophthalmic agent therapy that is delivered in the form of an eye drop.
Treatment by a class of drugs that treat erythropoietic protoporphyria.
A drug or substance given to inhibit VMAT2 for therapeutic uses.
Treatment with any coagulating factors that promote clotting.
Treatment with any drug or agent that regulates coenzymes.
Treatment with the drug thalidomide.
Treatment with the drug mevalonolactone.
Any drug or agent that lessens or prohibits myopathy.
Any drug or agent that inhibits carbonic anhydrase.
Any drug or agent that inhibits adrenergic uptake.
Avoid the administration or use of thalidomide agent therapy.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding cannabis consumption.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding tobacco consumption.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding smoking behavior.

label.value: consumption of an addictive substance avoidance

definition.value: A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding consumption of an addictive substance.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding agitation behavior.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding fear/anxiety related behavior.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding sexual activity.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding copulation.
A medical requirement or recommendation of avoiding stress related behavior.

value.value: Genetic testing of one or more cells removed from early embryos conceived by in vitro fertilization and transferring to the mother's uterus only those embryos determined not to have the pathogenic variant(s)/chromosome anomaly(ies) of concern.

definition.value: A procedure that can determine the DNA sequence for all of the exons (protein coding region) in an individual.

value.value: Clinical Exome Sequencing is a test for identifying disease-causing DNA variants within the 1% of the genome which codes for proteins (exons) or flanks the regions which code for proteins (splice junctions).
Sequence analysis of the exons of protein-coding genes in the genome typically performed by target enrichment or capture of exons followed by next-generation sequencing.

label.value: proctocolectomy with ileal pouch anal anastomosis

definition.value: The removal of the large intestine and rectum followed by making a pouch of the last part of the small intestine for solid material storage. The pouch is then sewn to the anus.
A procedure that can determine the DNA sequence for coding and non-coding regions in an individual.

value.value: Sequence analysis of the genome including coding and noncoding regions typically performed by next-generation sequencing (NGS) of sheared genomic DNA.

definition.value: Fetal echocardiography is a test that uses sound waves (ultrasound) to evaluate the structure and function of the fetus's heart.

An application of diagnostic ultrasound used to detect moving blood cells or other moving structures and measure their direction and speed of movement. The Doppler effect is used to evaluate movement by measuring changes in frequency of the echoes reflected from moving structures.
The use of ultrasound on a pregnant person to produce images of structures in the kidney of the fetus.
A surgical procedure where the whole colon is removed and the ileum is joined directly to the rectum.

value.value: Surgical removal of part of the pancreas, duodenum, and distal part of the bile duct. Sometimes, the lower portion of the stomach and the gallbladder are also removed. This procedure is performed for pancreatic, ampullary, duodenal and distal bile duct cancers.
Infusion of red blood cells into a fetus through the umbilical code.

definition.value: Use of a drug or therapy that block neuromuscular transmission, causing paralysis of the affected skeletal muscles.
